  "summary": "Malicious code in web3-deploy-helper (npm)",
  "details": "The package web3-deploy-helper@1.0.0 runs a postinstall script (postinstall.js) that steals Ethereum wallet credentials. On installation, it reads private keys, mnemonics, and seed phrases from.env files, hardhat config files, and environment variables. Harvested credentials are AES-encrypted and exfiltrated as transaction data in zero-value Ethereum transactions to address 0xCBbecC5E5Eb88582e6305cF6ab688f03e02Ce16f, using public RPC providers (eth[.]llamarpc[.]com, rpc[.]ankr[.]com/eth, ethereum[.]publicnode[.]com). The package index.js is an inert stub with no real functionality.",
